docs.abstract: A setback with India and continuing negotiations with the United States test Beijing’s talk of lowering global barriers.
docs.snippet: A setback with India and continuing negotiations with the United States test Beijing’s talk of lowering global barriers.
docs.lead_paragraph: SHANGHAI — Xi Jinping, China’s top leader, broadly endorsed free-trade principles and promised to welcome foreign investment in a speech on Tuesday, but a setback with India and a lack of details toward ending the punishing trade war with the United States are testing Beijing’s ability to prove it can make a deal.

headline.main: China’s Xi Praises Free Trade. Striking Deals Is Another Matter.
headline.print_headline: China Endorses Free Trade, But Finds Deals Are Elusive

docs.lead_paragraph: WeWork said on Thursday that it was laying off 2,400 employees around the world, weeks after huge losses at the co-working company brought it close to financial collapse.

docs.abstract: The suit claims Fiat Chrysler sought to undermine contract negotiations with the autoworkers union to hurt G.M.
docs.snippet: The suit claims Fiat Chrysler sought to undermine contract negotiations with the autoworkers union to hurt G.M.
docs.lead_paragraph: General Motors sued its rival Fiat Chrysler on Wednesday, asserting that it bribed United Auto Workers officials in contract negotiations to get a leg up on G.M. over the course of a decade.

headline.main: G.M. Sues Rival Over Bribery Scheme as Union Scandal Expands
headline.print_headline: In Filing Suit, G.M. Claims Fiat Chrysler Bribed Union

docs.abstract: “The Banker,” one of the tech giant’s first forays into film, was a day away from its premiere at AFI Fest in Los Angeles.
docs.snippet: “The Banker,” one of the tech giant’s first forays into film, was a day away from its premiere at AFI Fest in Los Angeles.
docs.lead_paragraph: Apple canceled the premiere of “The Banker,” starring Samuel L. Jackson, on Wednesday, yanking the movie from its prestigious closing-night Thursday slot at the American Film Institute’s annual festival in Los Angeles.

docs.abstract: The commission put new restrictions on money aimed at helping wireless carriers provide broadband to rural areas.

docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Federal Communications Commission voted on Friday to bar cellular carriers from using federal subsidies to buy equipment from Huawei and ZTE, two Chinese companies, saying the companies endangered national security.

docs.abstract: Donors don’t want their money misused or used less effectively than it could be. ImpactMatters joins several well-established rating sites.
docs.snippet: Donors don’t want their money misused or used less effectively than it could be. ImpactMatters joins several well-established rating sites.
docs.lead_paragraph: It has become the holy grail of philanthropy: measuring the impact of a charitable contribution. Donors don’t want their money misused or used less effectively than it could be, but how can impact be measured?

headline.main: New Rating System for Charities Aims to Measure Impact of Gifts
headline.print_headline: Is Your Money Helping? Check the Star Rating

docs.abstract: There is a lot to learn from mistakes that the Continent’s regulators have made, say consumer groups, lawyers and rival companies.
docs.snippet: There is a lot to learn from mistakes that the Continent’s regulators have made, say consumer groups, lawyers and rival companies.
docs.lead_paragraph: LONDON — Richard Stables should have felt vindicated when the European Union announced a $2.7 billion fine in 2017 against Google for breaking antitrust laws. He had raised alarms about the search giant’s power for years.

headline.main: Europe Is Toughest on Big Tech, Yet Big Tech Still Reigns
headline.print_headline: Tech Giants  Shrug Off Europe’s Bite
